Step 2: Import pandas libraries
Step 3: Load dataset into DataFrame
Step 4: Display data using head()
Step 5: Check missing values using isnull()
Step 6: Fill or remove missing values
Step 7: Remove duplicate rows
Step 8: Display cleaned data
Step 9: Use describe() for summary
Step 10: End


CODE
import pandas as pd

data = {
    'Name': ['Tanya', 'Shivani', 'Sundaram', None],
    'Marks': [85, 90, None, 75]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Original Data:")
print(df)

df['Name'].fillna("Sajan", inplace=True)
df['Marks'].fillna(df['Marks'].mean(), inplace=True)

df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)

print("\nCleaned Data:")
print(df)

print("\nSummary:")
print(df.describe())


